13#ifndef MODULES_CONGESTION_CONTROLLER_GOOG_CC_SEND_SIDE_BANDWIDTH_ESTIMATION_H_
14#define MODULES_CONGESTION_CONTROLLER_GOOG_CC_SEND_SIDE_BANDWIDTH_ESTIMATION_H_
15
16#include <stdint.h>
17
18#include <deque>
19#include <utility>
20#include <vector>
21
22#include "absl/types/optional.h"
23#include "api/transport/network_types.h"
24#include "api/transport/webrtc_key_value_config.h"
25#include "api/units/data_rate.h"
26#include "api/units/time_delta.h"
27#include "api/units/timestamp.h"
28#include "modules/congestion_controller/goog_cc/loss_based_bandwidth_estimation.h"
29#include "rtc_base/experiments/field_trial_parser.h"
30
31namespace webrtc {
32
33class RtcEventLog;
34
35class LinkCapacityTracker {
36 public:
37 LinkCapacityTracker();
38 ~LinkCapacityTracker();
39 // Call when a new delay-based estimate is available.
40 void UpdateDelayBasedEstimate(Timestamp at_time,
41 DataRate delay_based_bitrate);
42 void OnStartingRate(DataRate start_rate);
43 void OnRateUpdate(absl::optional<DataRate> acknowledged,
44 DataRate target,
45 Timestamp at_time);
46 void OnRttBackoff(DataRate backoff_rate, Timestamp at_time);
47 DataRate estimate() const;
48
49 private:
50 FieldTrialParameter<TimeDelta> tracking_rate;
51 double capacity_estimate_bps_ = 0;
52 Timestamp last_link_capacity_update_ = Timestamp::MinusInfinity();
53 DataRate last_delay_based_estimate_ = DataRate::PlusInfinity();
54};
55
56class RttBasedBackoff {
57 public:
58 explicit RttBasedBackoff(const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* key_value_config);
59 ~RttBasedBackoff();
60 void UpdatePropagationRtt(Timestamp at_time, TimeDelta propagation_rtt);
61 TimeDelta CorrectedRtt(Timestamp at_time) const;
62
63 FieldTrialFlag disabled_;
64 FieldTrialParameter<TimeDelta> configured_limit_;
65 FieldTrialParameter<double> drop_fraction_;
66 FieldTrialParameter<TimeDelta> drop_interval_;
67 FieldTrialParameter<DataRate> bandwidth_floor_;
68
69 public:
70 TimeDelta rtt_limit_;
71 Timestamp last_propagation_rtt_update_;
72 TimeDelta last_propagation_rtt_;
73 Timestamp last_packet_sent_;
74};
75
76class SendSideBandwidthEstimation {
77 public:
78 SendSideBandwidthEstimation() = delete;
79 SendSideBandwidthEstimation(const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* key_value_config,
80 RtcEventLog* event_log);
81 ~SendSideBandwidthEstimation();
82
83 void OnRouteChange();
84
85 DataRate target_rate() const;
86 uint8_t fraction_loss() const { return last_fraction_loss_; }
87 TimeDelta round_trip_time() const { return last_round_trip_time_; }
88
89 DataRate GetEstimatedLinkCapacity() const;
90 // Call periodically to update estimate.
91 void UpdateEstimate(Timestamp at_time);
92 void OnSentPacket(const SentPacket& sent_packet);
93 void UpdatePropagationRtt(Timestamp at_time, TimeDelta propagation_rtt);
94
95 // Call when we receive a RTCP message with TMMBR or REMB.
96 void UpdateReceiverEstimate(Timestamp at_time, DataRate bandwidth);
97
98 // Call when a new delay-based estimate is available.
99 void UpdateDelayBasedEstimate(Timestamp at_time, DataRate bitrate);
100
101 // Call when we receive a RTCP message with a ReceiveBlock.
102 void UpdatePacketsLost(int64_t packets_lost,
103 int64_t number_of_packets,
104 Timestamp at_time);
105
106 // Call when we receive a RTCP message with a ReceiveBlock.
107 void UpdateRtt(TimeDelta rtt, Timestamp at_time);
108
109 void SetBitrates(absl::optional<DataRate> send_bitrate,
110 DataRate min_bitrate,
111 DataRate max_bitrate,
112 Timestamp at_time);
113 void SetSendBitrate(DataRate bitrate, Timestamp at_time);
114 void SetMinMaxBitrate(DataRate min_bitrate, DataRate max_bitrate);
115 int GetMinBitrate() const;
116 void SetAcknowledgedRate(absl::optional<DataRate> acknowledged_rate,
117 Timestamp at_time);
118 void IncomingPacketFeedbackVector(const TransportPacketsFeedback& report);
119
120 private:
121 friend class GoogCcStatePrinter;
122
123 enum UmaState { kNoUpdate, kFirstDone, kDone };
124
125 bool IsInStartPhase(Timestamp at_time) const;
126
127 void UpdateUmaStatsPacketsLost(Timestamp at_time, int packets_lost);
128
129 // Updates history of min bitrates.
130 // After this method returns min_bitrate_history_.front().second contains the
131 // min bitrate used during last kBweIncreaseIntervalMs.
132 void UpdateMinHistory(Timestamp at_time);
133
134 // Gets the upper limit for the target bitrate. This is the minimum of the
135 // delay based limit, the receiver limit and the loss based controller limit.
136 DataRate GetUpperLimit() const;
137 // Prints a warning if |bitrate| if sufficiently long time has past since last
138 // warning.
139 void MaybeLogLowBitrateWarning(DataRate bitrate, Timestamp at_time);
140 // Stores an update to the event log if the loss rate has changed, the target
141 // has changed, or sufficient time has passed since last stored event.
142 void MaybeLogLossBasedEvent(Timestamp at_time);
143
144 // Cap |bitrate| to [min_bitrate_configured_, max_bitrate_configured_] and
145 // set |current_bitrate_| to the capped value and updates the event log.
146 void UpdateTargetBitrate(DataRate bitrate, Timestamp at_time);
147 // Applies lower and upper bounds to the current target rate.
148 // TODO(srte): This seems to be called even when limits haven't changed, that
149 // should be cleaned up.
150 void ApplyTargetLimits(Timestamp at_time);
151
152 RttBasedBackoff rtt_backoff_;
153 LinkCapacityTracker link_capacity_;
154
155 std::deque<std::pair<Timestamp, DataRate> > min_bitrate_history_;
156
157 // incoming filters
158 int lost_packets_since_last_loss_update_;
159 int expected_packets_since_last_loss_update_;
160
161 absl::optional<DataRate> acknowledged_rate_;
162 DataRate current_target_;
163 DataRate last_logged_target_;
164 DataRate min_bitrate_configured_;
165 DataRate max_bitrate_configured_;
166 Timestamp last_low_bitrate_log_;
167
168 bool has_decreased_since_last_fraction_loss_;
169 Timestamp last_loss_feedback_;
170 Timestamp last_loss_packet_report_;
171 uint8_t last_fraction_loss_;
172 uint8_t last_logged_fraction_loss_;
173 TimeDelta last_round_trip_time_;
174
175 // The max bitrate as set by the receiver in the call. This is typically
176 // signalled using the REMB RTCP message and is used when we don't have any
177 // send side delay based estimate.
178 DataRate receiver_limit_;
179 DataRate delay_based_limit_;
180 Timestamp time_last_decrease_;
181 Timestamp first_report_time_;
182 int initially_lost_packets_;
183 DataRate bitrate_at_2_seconds_;
184 UmaState uma_update_state_;
185 UmaState uma_rtt_state_;
186 std::vector<bool> rampup_uma_stats_updated_;
187 RtcEventLog* const event_log_;
188 Timestamp last_rtc_event_log_;
189 float low_loss_threshold_;
190 float high_loss_threshold_;
191 DataRate bitrate_threshold_;
192 LossBasedBandwidthEstimation loss_based_bandwidth_estimation_;
193 FieldTrialFlag receiver_limit_caps_only_;
194};
195} // namespace webrtc
196#endif // MODULES_CONGESTION_CONTROLLER_GOOG_CC_SEND_SIDE_BANDWIDTH_ESTIMATION_H_
